        <detaileddescription>
<para><computeroutput>httpForSse_</computeroutput> exists only as the backing <computeroutput>httplib::Client</computeroutput> that <computeroutput>sse_</computeroutput> holds by reference. We never call methods on it directly after the constructor configures its timeouts. We keep POSTs on a separate Client so (a) read timeouts can differ — SSE wants ~5 min long-poll, POST wants ~30 s — and (b) <computeroutput>sse_.stop()</computeroutput> (which internally calls <computeroutput>client_.stop()</computeroutput>) doesn&apos;t yank in-flight POSTs at gateway shutdown. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
